      "variant": "main",
      "html": "<h4>Activity</h4>\n<p><img alt=\"two cell phones\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/0c6bff83c63e52baf75d5df3584a14c21c65003d\" width=\"250\"></p>\n<p>The function \\(P\\) gives the number of people, in millions, who own a smartphone, \\(t\\) years after the year 2000. So, any value for which \\(t\\) is negative would represent the number of years before 2000.</p>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol>\n      <li>What does each equation tell us about smartphone ownership?\n        <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" type=\"a\">\n          <li>\\(P(17)=2320\\)</li>\n        </ol>\n      </li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>In 2017, about 2,320 million or 2.32 billion people owned a smartphone. </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol>\n      <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"2\" type=\"a\">\n        <li>\\(P(-10)=0\\)</li>\n      </ol>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answers:</p>\n    <p>No one owned a smartphone in 1990, 10 years before 2000.</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\"> <br>\n    <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"2\">\n      <li>Use function notation to represent each statement.\n        <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" type=\"a\">\n          <li>In 2010, the number of people who owned a smartphone was 296,600,000.</li>\n        </ol>\n      </li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>\\(P(10) = 296.6\\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\"> <br>\n    <ol>\n      <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"2\" type=\"a\">\n        <li>In 2015, about 1.86 billion people owned a smartphone.</li>\n      </ol>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>\\(P(15) = 1860\\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\"> <br>\n    <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"3\">\n      <li>Mai is curious about the value of \\(t\\) in \\(P(t)=1000\\).\n        <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" type=\"a\">\n          <li>What would the value of \\(t\\) tell Mai about the situation?</li>\n        </ol>\n      </li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answers:</p>\n    <p> the year when 1 billion people owned a smartphone (adding the value of \\(t\\) to 2000 gives the year)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\"> <br>\n    <ol>\n      <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"2\" type=\"a\">\n        <li>Is 4 a possible value of \\(t\\) here?</li>\n      </ol>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answers:</p>\n    <p>No. \\(t=4\\) corresponds to the year 2004. At that time, the number of smartphone owners should be below that of 2010, which was 296 million.</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-desmos-gc\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\"></div>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"Reveal1\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n    <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"4\">\n      <li>Use the graphing tool above or technology outside the course. Use the information you have so far to sketch a graph of the function.<br>\n        <br>\n        Your graph should go through these four points: \\((-10,0)\\), \\((10,296.6)\\), \\((15,1860)\\), and \\((17,2320)\\).\n      </li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n    <p>Then select the <strong>Solution</strong> button to compare your work.</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<br>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-content\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"Reveal1\">\n  <p>Compare your answers:</p>\n  <p><img alt=\"Nonlinear function. years since 2000 and population in millions.\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/4dac1bfb02e50aed4951b01ef5ff6311e029f0fa\"></p>\n</div>\n<!-- \"Start \"Are you Ready for More? click to reveal.  If you have more than one on a page, you will need to change the Data-fire/data-wait-for-events for each set.-->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Are you ready for more?\" data-fire-event=\"RFM1\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Start interaction.  If multiple interactions appear under \"are you ready for more?, they should all have matching \"data-wait-for-event\", which should also match the \"data-fire-event\" for the button. Note in this sample, they are all RFM1-->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"RFM1\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <h4>Extending Your Thinking </h4>\n    <p>What can you say about the value or values of \\(t\\) when \\(P(t)=1000\\)?</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answers: </p>\n    <p>There is not enough information to know exactly when 1 billion (1,000 million) people owned a smartphone, but there is likely only one value of \\(t\\) when \\(P(t)=1000\\), and that value is somewhere between 10 and 15. This is because the number of smartphone users was less than a billion in 2010 and more than a billion in 2015. </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--End interaction-->"
    }
